SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 1094
By Jackson
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Chansler Yarbrough
upon being named the 2026 Boys & Girls Club
of Jackson Youth of the Year.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly pause in their
deliberations to salute those young citizens who, through their remarkable efforts, have
distinguished themselves as emerging community and state leaders of whom we can all be
proud; and
WHEREAS, one such deserving person is Chansler Yarbrough, who was recently
named the 2026 Boys & Girls Club of Jackson Youth of the Year; and
WHEREAS, Mr. Yarbrough, a student at Northside High School, has been a member of
the Boys & Girls Club of Jackson for six years; and
WHEREAS, the Boys & Girls Clubs exist to serve youth and provide a safe place of
encouragement, character building, security, and love for children; and
WHEREAS, since 1947, the Youth of the Year honor has been the Boys & Girls Clubs of
America's premier recognition program, celebrating the extraordinary achievements of Club
members; and
WHEREAS, Youth of the Year participants such as Chansler Yarbrough exemplify the
critical impact of Boys & Girls Clubs on the lives of young people, embodying the values of
leadership, service, academic excellence, and healthy lifestyles; and
WHEREAS, through the Youth of the Year program, Mr. Yarbrough and other Youth of
the Year participants are able to showcase their talents and achievements, share their hopes
and dreams, and work toward a bright and positive future; and
WHEREAS, Chansler Yarbrough is a shining example that "GREAT FUTURES START
HERE" at Boys & Girls Clubs; and
SJR1094
017420
- 1 -

WHEREAS, the success of this State, the strength of our communities, and the overall
vitality of American society depend, in great measure, upon the dedication of young people such
as Chansler Yarbrough, who use their considerable talents and resources to serve others and
who should be specially recognized for their public and community service; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Chansler Yarbrough upon
being named the 2026 Boys & Girls Club of Jackson Youth of the Year and extend to him our
best wishes for every future success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
